 out further objects that are more massive than 6 MJup, and for projected separations {$\rho$} {$>$} 2 we are sensitive to planets with masses as low as 2 MJup. Conclusions. YSES 2b is an ideal target for follow-up observations to further the understanding of the physical and chemical formation mechanisms of wide-orbit Jovian planets. The YSES strategy of short snapshot observations ({$\leq$}5 min) and PSF subtraction based on a large reference library proves to be extremely efficient and should be considered for future direct imaging surveys.},
