e. We confirm previous findings that the abundance of \textsuperscript{7{$<$}sup/{$>$}Li in the solar neighbourhood does not decrease at super-solar metallicity. The comparison of the data with the chemical evolution model predictions favours a scenario in which the majority of the \textsuperscript{7{$<$}sup/{$>$}Li abundance in meteorites comes from novae. Current data also seem to suggest that the nova rate flattens out at later times. This requirement might have implications for the masses of the white dwarf nova progenitors and deserves further investigation. Neutrino-induced reactions taking place in core-collapse supernovae also produce some fresh lithium. This likely makes a negligible contribution to the meteoritic abundance, but could be responsible for a mild increase in the \textsuperscript{7{$<$}sup/{$>$}Li abundance in the ISM of low-metallicity systems that would counterbalance the astration processes.}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}},
