s shows a drop of nearly three orders of magnitude for the luminosity in these bands between~{$\sim$}10\,Myr and few\,Gyr age. A few young field dwarfs (\&lt;1\,Gyr) in the 10-pc sample bridge the gap indicating that the drop in magnetic activity with age is a continuous process. The slope of the age decay is steeper for the X-ray than for the UV luminosity.},
